    "desc": "Voice of Witness (VOW) advances human rights by amplifying the voices of people impacted by—and fighting against—injustice.",
    "navbar": "",
    "text": "Skip to content\nABOUT\nBOOKS\nEDUCATION\nNEWS\nGET INVOLVED\nDONATE\nLearn More\nNewsletter\nDonate\nWe produce an acclaimed book series that depicts human rights and social justice issues through the edited oral histories of people who are most deeply impacted and whose lived experiences are at the heart of finding solutions.\nOur education program connects educators, students, and members of justice movements around the U.S. with these stories and issues through oral history-based curricula, training, and holistic educational support.\nChecking In With VOW Narrators: Where Are They Now?\nSharing Our Methodology: Oral History Workshop with Nearpod\n100cameras Program Impact: Students Sharing Stories and Building Empathy\nRead more from our blog.\nFOLLOW US\nSUPPORT VOICE OF WITNESS\nOur work is made possible through support from individual donors, foundations, and community partners.\nIf you would like to help us tell these important stories, please consider making a tax-deductible donation or volunteering.\nSUPPORT\nHelp us tell these crucial stories. Donate today.\nSUBSCRIBE\nSign up for the VOW Newsletter for monthly updates from Voice of Witness. Get the latest news on book projects, events, and new resources.\nContact\nP.O. Box 297\nSan Francisco, CA 94104-0297\n\nContact Staff\nFOLLOW\n© 2022 Voice of Witness | All Rights Reserved",
